cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.CR, cs.FL, cs.HC

The paper deals with iris recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). It also involves biometrics and security (cs.CR), forensic science (cs.FL), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it deals with post-mortem human subjects. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CV and cs.IR, followed by cs.CR, cs.FL, and cs.HC.
